item.description:
invalid: <p>
Don't think this is possible. <code>wpautop()</code> is run on the HTML string before it is loaded in the editor. To initialize wpView we need the editor DOM that was created by loading that HTML string.
</p>
<p>
See the note in the code:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">// When the editor's content has been updated and the DOM has been
// processed, render the views in the document.
editor.on( 'SetContent', function() {
        wp.mce.views.render();
});
</pre>
